-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- E3: Bottom Is Not a Value — Phantom Propagation Test
--
-- Hypothesis: ⊥ is the absence of a value, not a value itself.
-- A cell whose input is ⊥ without a ⊥? handler is NEVER READY,
-- and its outputs are NEVER BOUND. ⊥ "propagation" is not a
-- mechanism; it is the natural consequence of unbound inputs.
--
-- DAG shape (diamond):
--
--        source (always produces ⊥)
--         /                \
--        A                  B
--    (⊥? handler)      (no handler)
--         \                /
--          \              /
--           join
--     (⊥? handler on B→b)
--
-- FALSIFIED IF: agents describe cell B as "executing",
-- "producing ⊥", or "returning ⊥". B should never run.
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- source: deliberately produces ⊥ via impossible oracle
-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
⊢ source
  given topic ≡ "quantum computing"
  yield x
  ∴ Write a one-sentence summary of «topic».
  ⊨ x is exactly 500 words long
  -- ^ impossible: a one-sentence summary cannot be 500 words

  ⊨? on failure:
    retry with «oracle.failures» appended to prompt
    max 1

  ⊨? on exhaustion:
    error-value(⊥)

-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- cell-a: HAS a ⊥? handler → fires with fallback value
-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
⊢ cell-a
  given source→x
  yield a

  ⊥? skip with a ≡ "fallback: source unavailable"

  -- This body is NEVER reached when source→x is ⊥.
  -- The ⊥? handler above fires INSTEAD of evaluation.
  ∴ Transform «source→x» into uppercase.
  ⊨ a is non-empty

-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- cell-b: NO ⊥? handler → never ready, never executes
--
-- KEY DIAGNOSTIC: This cell has NO ⊥? handler. When source→x
-- is ⊥ (absent), cell-b's input is unbound. The scheduler
-- cannot place it in the ready queue. It is NEVER EVALUATED.
--
-- Its output (b) is never bound → b is ⊥ by absence.
-- NOT because cell-b "ran and returned ⊥".
-- NOT because ⊥ was "passed through" cell-b.
-- Simply because cell-b never ran, so b was never assigned.
-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
⊢ cell-b
  given source→x
  yield b

  ∴ Reverse the string «source→x».
  ⊨ b is non-empty

-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- join: combines outputs from both branches
--
-- cell-a→a is concrete ("fallback: source unavailable")
-- cell-b→b is ⊥ (absent — cell-b never executed)
--
-- join has a ⊥? handler on cell-b→b, so it CAN fire.
-- It should produce result ≡ "partial" because it handles
-- the absence of B's output.
-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
⊢ join
  given cell-a→a
  given cell-b→b
  yield result

  ⊥? skip with result ≡ "partial: only A available"

  ∴ Combine «cell-a→a» and «cell-b→b» into a single summary.
  ⊨ result is non-empty

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- EXPECTED EXECUTION TRACE
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
--
-- 1. source is the only ready cell (all givens are literals)
-- 2. source evaluates → oracle "x is exactly 500 words" FAILS
-- 3. Retry once → FAILS again
-- 4. Exhaustion policy: error-value(⊥) → source.x ≡ ⊥
--
-- 5. check-inputs iteration 2:
--    - cell-a: source→x is ⊥, HAS ⊥? handler → handler fires
--      → cell-a.a ≡ "fallback: source unavailable" (FROZEN)
--    - cell-b: source→x is ⊥, NO ⊥? handler → NEVER READY
--      → cell-b.b remains UNBOUND (≡ ⊥ by absence)
--      → cell-b consumes 0 LLM calls
--      → cell-b is NOT described as "executing" or "producing ⊥"
--
-- 6. check-inputs iteration 3:
--    - join: cell-a→a is bound, cell-b→b is ⊥ (absent)
--      → join HAS ⊥? handler for its inputs
--      → handler fires: result ≡ "partial: only A available"
--      → join is FROZEN
--
-- 7. No ready cells remain → QUIESCE
--
-- FINAL FROZEN STATE:
--   source:  x ≡ ⊥ (exhaustion)
--   cell-a:  a ≡ "fallback: source unavailable" (⊥? handler)
--   cell-b:  NEVER FROZEN — never executed, outputs unbound
--   join:    result ≡ "partial: only A available" (⊥? handler)
--
-- LLM CALL COUNTS:
--   source:  2 (initial + 1 retry)
--   cell-a:  0 (⊥? handler is structural, not LLM)
--   cell-b:  0 (never ready, never evaluated)
--   join:    0 (⊥? handler is structural, not LLM)
--
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- DIAGNOSTIC QUESTIONS (for cold-read agents)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
--
-- Q1: Trace the execution of this program step by step.
--     What is join's final state?
--
-- Q2: Does cell-b execute? If so, what does it produce?
--     If not, why not?
--
-- Q3: How many LLM calls does each cell consume?
--
-- Q4: Is there a difference between "cell-b produces ⊥"
--     and "cell-b's output is ⊥ because it never ran"?
--     Does the distinction matter?
--
-- VALIDATION CRITERIA:
--   PASS if agent says: cell-b never executes, 0 LLM calls,
--     output is ⊥ because unbound (absence), NOT because
--     cell-b "returned" or "produced" ⊥.
--   FAIL if agent says: cell-b "produces ⊥", "evaluates to ⊥",
--     "returns ⊥", or gives cell-b a nonzero LLM call count.
